### ENV: Ubuntu / Visual Studio Code / Python / GIT

### Ubuntu installation
  1 Download Ubuntu desktop-version (Ubuntu n.n LTS image) @ https://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop
  2 Download Rufus tool @ https://rufus.ie/en_IE.html
  3 Create bootable Ubuntu USB stick using Rufus tool
  4 Boot your desktop/laptop using USB and follow instructions to install Ubuntu

### Steps to install Visual Studio Code & configure for python
  1 Goto https://code.visualstudio.com/ and download for Ubuntu platform and install
  2 Next install Python extension for VS Code
  3 Ensure pip3 is installed (whereis pip3)
  4 Install pylint (sudo pip3 install pylint)
  5 REFERENCE: https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/python/python-tutorial

### Steps to install GIT
  1 sudo apt-get install git
  2 goto https://github.com and create an account there
  3 git config --global user.name "ur-git-name"
  4 git config --global user.email "xyz@gmail.com"
  5 create a repo at the github website
  6 in local folder use git init
  7 git remote add origin https://github.com/user/repo.git
  # YouTube: Linux Tutorials - How to Install and Configure Git & Repositorys on GitHub

### Steps to clone GIT repo on a different machine
    goto desired project folder and:
  1 git clone https://github.com/ur-name/ur-repo.git
    create new file
  2 git add .
  3 git commit -m "new file added"
  4 git push origin master
  5 git pull origin master

### Steps to setup GIT branch (file states: modified / staged /committed)
  # goto project root folder:
  1 git init
  2 git add filename.ext
  3 git commit -m "check-in-msg"
  # for github use:
  4 git push origin master
  4 git status
  5 git checkout -- filename.ext
# e.g. $ git clone git://github.com/pbatard/rufus
